social_posts.post_text: Just a tiny snippet of my 2022 season. Thank you, as always, to my incredible clients for trusting me to document the most precious moments of your lives. I can’t wait to see what 2023 brings!!

Christmas time and blossom season really are tied up for my favorite time of the year. With all of this rain we’ve been having, I think the sunshine and white blooms are really going to be such a happy relief from the gloomy days (that I’m already very much over).

With all of this said, expect some mini session info soon for these beauties!
Kicking off my 2023 season with these lovebirds tomorrow and I couldn’t be happier!
From their engagement session to welcoming their baby girl, I’ve been lucky enough to capture so many of their most precious moments and I couldn’t be happier. Welcome to the world, sweet Ella 🤍

After two (what felt like) very long weeks of my adorable children being home from preschool, they went back today and mama had a nice day out with the bff. Feeling so refreshed and recharged and ready to get back to work and editing. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I will say though, I’m missing our great California sunshine. It feels like this rain will never end! So I’m reminiscing back to this sunny fall day when Kelsey and Ben said I do, part two!

I’ve realized that as soon as Christmas is taken down and all of the gingerbread cookies have been eaten, I start craving spring. It’s cold and gloomy and I long for sunshine and some sort of a hint of a bloom. I think that’s why almond blossom season brings me so much joy.

While I’m sitting in my cold office, I’m daydreaming about our @themilkandhoneyevent styled series and this beautiful session. Here’s to springtime and more beautiful things to photograph this year!

But, back to weddings. I’m taking maaaaaybe 1-2 more for fall of 2023 and my 2024 calendar is now officially open. 

*Priority weddings would be in destinations with macarons, gelato, warm, sunny beaches and fresh margaritas 😉

What I’m currently working on.

These sweet ones 🤍
There are a lot of babies coming to my circle of friends this summer and holy smokes I can’t wait for all of those tiny snuggles.

It’s engagement season clearly because I’m shot an engagement session every weekend for the past few weeks and I have another this weekend! Just so excited for all of these 2023 couples and the beautiful weddings I get to capture for them 🤍

I know I just announced blossom minis and have talked about wildflower sessions but I’m already racking my brain to figure out what I want to do for Mother’s Day sessions this year. I loved this setup so much from last year. (Those beautiful flowers from @sweetmemoriesflowers really stole the show) and can’t wait to celebrate and photograph all of you deserving mamas!

There are two times a year where I make sure my own family is documented; during blossoms and in the fall. But the blossoms may just be my favorite. I can’t wait until this years session with my little crew because my goodness the boys have grown so much in the last year 🤍🌸
Happy Valentine’s Day to all of the lovers out there 🤍

Weather is one of the biggest things that we as photographers have to fight against. Whether it’s rain during blossom season or wind at the beach. But somehow, we always manage and let the wind work in our favor, or just create unforgettable photos, ahem, like the last photo in this grouping. I think the Kalender crew wins for dealing with the craziest winds during a session!

In honor of this gorgeous wedding being on the cover of @visalialifestyle’s Wedding Edition, I figured it needed another permanent place on my feed. Thankful for an A+ team of vendors making the day beautiful from start to finish and an amazing couple, trusting us all 🤍

Wedding day tip from your friendly photographer…

PLEASE don’t forget about the men. The Groom and Groomsmen usually get left in the dark (LITERALLY) for getting ready photos and I swear most of the rooms they get put into are actual caves. They deserve beautifully lit spaces, too.

I’m a simple girl, really. I just am happiest when there’s an open field, a giant 300 year old oak tree, gorgeous florals and rolling vineyards. Like, super simple. Promise 😉
We all know my love for golden, dead grass but my heart is a little bit missing the soft green grass and wildflowers right now. Can it be springtime again?
Talking about minis in my stories today and we all know this dreamy location is always on my list.

Take me to your private ranch for your sessions always, please

A personal post

If I’m slower to respond to emails, or my feed isn’t as updated as I’d like it to be, this is why. If I’m not shooting 35 weddings a year (I’ve never wanted that, to be honest lol) or I’m not attending the latest workshop or summit, this is why. 

These three tiny humans are currently taking up every inch of my heart, and brain space, let’s be real. But they’re only little for so long and I know they’ll start needing me less and less as the years go on and I can get more and more me time and get back to doing more of what I love to do. 

But for now, this is a season. One I’ll never regret taking a little extra time for.

I promise my calendar will open up again and I’ll start traveling again soon to see all of my favorites. Thank you so much for sticking around 😉

If you’re not at a wedding today, like I feel so many are, then I hope you’re enjoying your Saturday!
